   <widget class="QTextEdit" name="textEdit_3">
    <property name="enabled">
     <bool>false</bool>
    </property>
    <property name="geometry">
     <rect>
      <x>570</x>
      <y>190</y>
      <width>411</width>
      <height>441</height>
     </rect>
    </property>
    <property name="styleSheet">
     <string notr="true">
    QTextEdit {
        background: transparent;
        font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
        font-size: 10pt;
        border: none;
    }
</string>
    </property>
    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;In 1896, the Philippine Revolution began, and Rizal’s name became linked to the growing independence movement. His novels, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Noli Me Tangere&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'MS Shell Dlg 2'; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;El Filibusterismo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, were viewed by the Spanish as sources of inspiration for the unrest, even though Rizal consistently promoted peaceful reform over rebellion. Later that year, he was arrested and falsely accused of inciting the revolution and collaborating with the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Katipunan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, a revolutionary group led by &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Andres Bonifacio.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Despite the absence of evidence connecting him to the uprising, the Spanish authorities, fearing the impact of his ideas, used his arrest to suppress the nationalist movement. Rizal’s execution on December 30, 1896, turned him into a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;martyr&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; for the cause, galvanizing Filipino revolutionaries and fueling the final phase of the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Philippine Revolution&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, which ultimately achieved the nation’s independence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
    </property>
   </widget>
